resources.string: When adjusting the screen brightness, you need to turn off the automatic brightness adjustment function of the system. The minimum adjustment can be -70, and the maximum adjustment can be 255. From small to large, from left to right, this function requires su permission, and it is normal to fail to adjust to a negative value. The device may not support negative value adjustment.

90hz has two options. Selecting shell means that only the shell command will be executed, and the front-end service will not be started. Selecting service means that only the front-end service will be started, and the shell command will not be executed.

There are two options for 120hz. Selecting shell means only executing shell commands and will not start the foreground service. Selecting service means only starting the foreground service and will not execute shell commands.

144hz has two options. Selecting shell means only executing shell commands and will not start the foreground service. Selecting service means only starting the foreground service and will not execute shell commands.

165hz has two options. Selecting shell means that only the shell command will be executed, and the front-end service will not be started. Selecting service means that only the front-end service will be started, and the shell command will not be executed.

There are two options for 200hz. Selecting shell means only executing shell commands and will not start the foreground service. Selecting service means only starting the foreground service and will not execute shell commands.
